OL,3,CLiverpool manager target Alonso to
OL,4,Cstay in Germany
OL,6,FHopes had been high at Anfield that
OL,7,Fthe 42-year-old, who played 210 games
OL,8,Ffor the Reds between 2004 and 2009 and
OL,9,Fwon the Champions League during his
OL,10,Ffirst campaign, would take over from
OL,11,FKlopp when he steps down in the summer.
OL,13,FHowever, those plans have been
OL,14,Fscuppered by Alonso's decision to stay
OL,15,Fand build on what looks to be a first-
OL,16,Fever title for the BayArena side.
OL,18,F"I'm in the right place here," he said
OL,19,Fat his press conference to preview the
OL,20,Fweekend clash with Hoffenheim. "I'll
OL,21,Fstay with Bayer.
