OL,6,FThe development forces Liverpool to
OL,7,Fconsider alternative candidates to
OL,8,Fsucceed the German, who has won the
OL,9,FPremier League and Champions League
OL,10,Fduring his near nine seasons in charge.
OL,12,FSporting Lisbon boss Ruben Amorim and
OL,13,FBrighton's Roberto De Zerbi are the
OL,14,Ftwo names most strongly linked with
OL,15,Fthe job.
OL,17,FAlonso had been courted by another of
OL,18,Fhis former clubs, Bayern Munich, who
OL,19,Fare in search of a manager with Thomas
OL,20,FTuchel due to step down at the end of
OL,21,Fthe season.
